Package: bayescomp
Title: Bayesian Hierarchical Comparison of Computational Method Benchmarks
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Rohit", "Goswami", email = "rgoswami@ieee.org",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-2393-8056"))
Description: A targets-integrated workflow for fitting Bayesian hierarchical
    models to computational method benchmarks. Supports negative binomial
    (count data), Gamma (timing), Bernoulli (success), and Student-t
    (signed errors) families with
    random intercepts per test system. Provides automated family selection,
    weakly informative prior defaults, convergence diagnostics, LOO-CV,
    posterior predictive checks, and publication-quality effect summaries.
    Built on 'brms' and 'cmdstanr'.
